description*.en: Sound Volume Velocity is the product of particle velocity $v$ and the surface area $S$ through which an acoustic wave of frequency $f$ propagates. Also, the surface integral of the normal component of the sound particle velocity over the cross-section (through which the sound propagates). It is used to calculate acoustic impedance.
